An '''Anstalt''' or '''Anstalt partnership''' is a type of [[incorporation (business)|incorporated organisation]].<ref>[[FATF]] guidance: Transparency and Beneficial Ownership,(October 2014) [http://www.fatf-gafi.org/media/fatf/documents/reports/Guidance-transparency-beneficial-ownership.pdf page 14].</ref>
==Characteristics== An Anstalt is a hybrid between a [[Proprietary company|company limited by shares]] and a [[stiftung|foundation]].<ref>[http://global-money.com/item.php?id=119 Going Offshore : Liechtenstein "ANSTALT" (Establishment) ].</ref> An Anstalt is an entity, which has no members,<ref>In this Anstalt are seen as in contrast to the more common corporate entity, [[Gesellschaft mit beschränkter Haftung]], found in many [[German language|German-speaking]] countries.</ref> participants or [[shareholder]]s.<ref>[http://pointonpartners.com.au/tax-residence-of-individuals-companies/ Tax Residence of Individuals & Companies] April 07, 2016.</ref> It differs from a company in that it has no duty to return [[profit (accounting)|profit]] and differs from a [[Trust law|trust]] in that it has no obligation to a [[beneficiary]].<ref>[http://global-money.com/item.php?id=119 Going Offshore : Liechtenstein "ANSTALT" (Establishment) ].</ref> Anstalt do have, however, a holder of the founder’s rights. The founder can be either a [[Legal personality|legal person]] or a [[natural person]], need not be resident in the host country and Anstalt must have a minimum capital of CHF 30 000 (approximately USD 33 800).<ref>[https://star.worldbank.org/star/sites/star/files/liechtenstein_-_afar_bo_country_guide_final.pdf An Investigator’S Guide To Company Ownership Information In Liechtenstein] ([[UNODC]]) p3.</ref> There is also no need for the founder identity to be notified to the registration office.
These features, and the founders rights, and because an Anstalt can conduct many kinds of business, including non-trading activities (such as holding passive investments), has made them popular with foreign companies who use them as a [[holding company]] for overseas subsidiaries when trying to minimise tax in their home jurisdictions. That is Anstalt are a safe/easy place to park assets at tax time.
===Types=== There are two types of Anstalt; commercial and non-commercial, and they feature prominently in the finance system of [[Liechtenstein]],<ref>[https://star.worldbank.org/star/sites/star/files/liechtenstein_-_afar_bo_country_guide_final.pdf An Investigator’S Guide To Company Ownership Information In Liechtenstein] (UNODC) p7.</ref> where they are considered to be a [[Public Law]] Institution, though they are not able to be listed on the [[Stock Exchange]].<ref>Claus-Dieter Ehlermann, Michelle Everson, European Competition Law Annual 1999: Selected Issues in the Field of State Aids (Bloomsbury Publishing, 2001) [https://books.google.com.au/books?id=p9zbBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA368&lpg=PA368&dq=Anstalt+partnership+definition&source=bl&ots=b06Dk2wamL&sig=X3LzQu4x9rL9jZgRz_cPsaWojAg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjAiv3QpMrSAhUTtJQKHcIZB4U4ChDoAQgbMAE#v=onepage&q=Anstalt%20partnership%20definition&f=false p368].</ref>
===Differences and uniqueness=== Anstalt differ from the related entities called [[stiftung]] in that Anstalt can conduct all kinds of business activities. Anstalt are seen as different to [[Gesellschaft mit beschränkter Haftung]], a corporate type found in many [[German language|German-speaking]] countries, which do feature members and participants.
Anstalt are a [[civil law (legal system)|civil law]] creation and no direct [[common law]] analogue exists.<ref>Robert Gordon TEP, [http://pointonpartners.com.au/international-inheritance-wealth-planning-issues/ International Inheritance & Wealth Planning Issues] (May 07, 2015).</ref>[[Common law]] courts have tended to treat Anstalt that are “limited by shares”, as a company, and those without shares (the majority) are sometimes (though not always<ref>see ''[[ashburn anstalt v Arnold]]'' 1989 ch 1 ca.</ref>) treated as a [[constructive trust]].<ref>see ''[[McGhee v National Coal Board]]'', [1972] 3 All E.R. 1008, 1 W.L.R. 1.</ref>
