==Etymology== The name Anstalt means ''Institution" or "Establishment''.<ref>[http://dictionary.reverso.net/german-english/Anstalt Anstalt translation | German-English dictionary].</ref> which comes from the [[Middle High German]] Anstalt and means to set up'' [Public] purpose for a particular purpose and the building which houses it.''<ref>[https://translate.google.com.au/translate?hl=en&sl=de&u=http://www.duden.de/rechtschreibung/Anstalt&prev=search Institution, the Word type: ℹ noun, feminine ] at Duden.de.</ref> ==See also== *[[Beneficial ownership]] *[[Holding company]]
