[[File:Kanun-i Esasi.jpg|thumb|left|Ottoman constitution of 1876]] {{Politics of Turkey}} {{History of Turkey}} Over the centuries, [[Turkey]] has had many [[constitution]]s and can be characterized by the steady establishment of a [[nation-state]], [[democratization]] and recognition of [[international law]].
The Turkish constitution was ratified in [[Turkish Constitution of 1921|1921]], revised in [[Turkish Constitution of 1924|1924]], [[Turkish Constitution of 1961|1961]], [[Turkish Constitution of 1982|1982]], and most recently in 2010.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://global.tbmm.gov.tr/docs/constitution_en.pdf|title=Constitution Of The Republic Of Turkey|last=The Grand National Assembly of Turkey|first=|date=2016-07-15|website=Constitution Of The Republic Of Turkey|publisher=The Grand National Assembly of Turkey|at=Chapter Three, Section I, Article 41, Para 3-4|access-date=2016-07-15}}</ref> A proposal for yet another constitution is being discussed, to allow Turkey to comply with [[Accession of Turkey to the European Union|EU accession]] political criteria.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cnnturk.com/Turkiye/anayasa.asp |title=Draft proposal |accessdate=2008-01-01 |year=2007|language=tr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Yavuz |first=Ercan |publisher=Zaman |url=http://www.todayszaman.com/tz-web/detaylar.do?load=detay&link=130544 |title=New constitution to dominate 2008 |date=2008-01-01 |accessdate=2008-01-01}}</ref>
==Milestones== [[File:London news c1877 - scanned constantinopole(1996)-Opening of the first parlement.png|thumb|Opening of the first [[Ottoman parliament]], (Meclis-i Umumî), 1877.]] * 1808: [[Charter of Alliance|Sened-i İttifak]] prepared by [[Alemdar Mustafa Pasha]], in period of [[Mahmut II]] was signed on September 29, among Rumelian and Anatolian chief men and the Ottoman State in order to make the central authority dominant over the provinces. * 1839: [[Imperial Edict of Reorganization]] prepared by [[Mustafa Reshid Pasha]] on November 3, during the rule of [[Abdülmecid I|Abdülmecit]]. * 1856: [[Hatt-ı Hümayun of 1856|Hatt-ı Hümayun]] that a complementary and reinforcing edict by Abdülmecit. * 1876: [[Ottoman constitution of 1876]], during the [[First Constitutional Era]] of the [[Ottoman Empire]] (1876–78). * 1909: Revisions to the 1876 constitution during the [[Second Constitutional Era]] of the Ottoman Empire (1908–20). * 1921: [[Turkish Constitution of 1921|1921 Constitution]]; first constitution of the Republic of Turkey; introduced a single chamber of legislation, the [[Grand National Assembly of Turkey|Grand National Assembly]], to form a [[Unicameralism|unicameral]] system. * 1924: [[Turkish Constitution of 1924|Revised constitution of 1924]]. * 1961: [[Turkish Constitution of 1961|1961 constitution]]; introduced an upper chamber of legislation, the [[Senate of the Republic (Turkey)|Senate]], to form a [[Bicameralism|bicameral]] system. * 1982: [[Constitution of Turkey|1982 constitution]]; abolished the Senate, reverting to a unicameral system. * 2017: Revisions to the 1982 constitution; introduced a [[presidential system]]; abolished the office of [[Prime Minister of Turkey|Prime Minister]].
