{{italic title}} '''''Tomson v. Ward''''' [[Case citation|1 N.H. 9 (1816)]] was the first [[New Hampshire Supreme Court]] decision recorded in the official New Hampshire [[Law reporter|reports]].
==Ruling== In the case the New Hampshire Supreme Court ruled that "[a]n unrecorded [[deed]] of lands voluntarily given up, and cancelled by the parties to it, with intent to [[revest]] the estate in the grantor, as between them and as to all subsequent claimants under them, operates as a [[reconveyance]], and revests the estate in the [[Conveyancing#United States|grantor]]."<ref>''Thomson v. Ward'', 1 N.H. 9 (1816)</ref>
